cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.HC 

This paper deals with automatic recognition and prediction of surgical activities, which involves analyzing and understanding visual and textual data related to surgical procedures. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV), natural language processing (cs.CL), and machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of knowledge transfer to compensate for data deficit, which is a common problem in healthcare applications. This makes the paper relevant to the human-computer interaction (cs.HC) sub-category as well.
